eNCA's John Bailey has the story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Pensioners are becoming increasingly important in the South African economy. Data shows that banked private pensions are growing at almost double the take-home pay rate. With the country's population ageing rapidly, pensioners will become more important in terms of their buying power. READ:Â Negative outlook for the economy in 2020 Pensions have been increasing since 2013 and have helped senior citizens survive the weak economy relatively well.South Africa's population is growing at an estimated 1.6 percent. At the same time, the segment of people over 60 years of age is growing at 3.4 percent, making pensioners the fastest-growing expenditure group in the country.